snippet.textDisplay: First girl was literally the same as me.. I’m 5’7” and my hair was to my butt, (my hair is hella fine, so imagine the tangles🙃.. I’d have a rats nest at the nape of my neck if I was out and about for an entire day with no brush..) and I cut my hair off to just above my shoulders.. lol I surprisingly didn’t freak like I thought I would.. my hair grows decently fast, so I wasn’t too tore up about it. I love my short hair .. that is until I see pics of my long hair, but I just gotta remind myself of how bad of a struggle I had with it being so long.. I do plan on letting it grow back out or getting extensions for when I want hella length again lmao

snippet.textDisplay:
Jeez, i LOVE that pink shirt! ♥

Imaging dealing with all of that hair? Well, mine is a bit longer than the first girl, but sadly i have thinner hair than her. I need like, 6 minutes in the morning dealing with it. When i am slow. Hardest thing is to decide what i will put into my hair as i have a bunch of different "hairtoys". If i need to rush, i need less than 3 minutes. Including all, combing and styling.

All of my short haired friends need so much more time for their hair and still try to argue that "short hair is so much easier and faster". Nope. It is not, You need a ton of sh*t to put in, styling iron, need to wash it like daily... That is not fast and not easy in care.

Only downside is that i really want to go to a hair dresser, for trimming the edges and having the "spa feeling" of someone else washing my hair, but sadly all hair dressers are the same, they always wanna cut it short, trying to coax me into a shorter haircut over and over again. And when they say "just 1 inch!" they take off 3-4 inches. Thanks, but no thanks!

(For those curious: My hair is nearly 40 inches long)
